<h3>1.3 Intro to Tags</h3>
<p>An HTML element is defined by a start tag, some content, and an end tag.</p> <p>Refer to the complete <a href="https://www.w3schools.com/tags/default.asp">List</a> of HTML tags </p>

<h2>Day 1 Code 2</h2>
<h3>1.3 Attributes: Intro & general practices</h3>
<p> -HTML attributes provide additional information about HTML elements<br>-They're always specified in the start tag of an element <br>-Usually come in name/value pairs like: name="value"</P>
<p>(a) <b>lang:</b> Always incorporate the "lang" attribute with its country code inside the <"html"> tag to declare the language of the Web page.<br>This is meant to assist search engines and browsers.<br></P>
<p>(b)<b>style:</b> This attribute is used to format the element with respect to its size/color/font. It can be used to set the theme of the web page. </p>
<p title="Additional info">(b)<b>title:</b> The value of the title attribute will be displayed as a tooltip when you hover mouse over the element.<br> Check it out now! hover the mouse on the <b>title</b> to see this attribute work </p>

